      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But I say unto you ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— You may perhaps think God does not much regard your words, but I assure you, that not only for blasphemous and profane, malicious, false, slanderous, and reviling words, but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for every idle word which men shall speak: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for all light, vain, trifling expressions; for all useless, unprofitable conversation, and all discourse uttered without seriousness and caution, and which does not conduce to the glory of God and the good of mankind; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that men shall speak ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— At any time, or on any occasion, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "they shall give an account in the day of judgment ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— “I cannot think,” says Dr. Doddridge, “that our Lord here uses ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αργον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "idle, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "merely to signify ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mischievous. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We are certainly accountable for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "useless ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as well as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wicked ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "discourses, and they will be taken into that last survey which is to determine our character and state: which they whose life is one continued scene of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whim, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sneering raillery, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "would do well seriously to consider. And it was to our Lord’s purpose to observe it here, as it inferred, by the strongest consequence, the danger of such vile and criminal discourses as those of the Pharisees in this case. But discourse tending to exhilarate the spirits is not idle discourse; as the time spent in necessary recreation is not idle time; nor does a wise and gracious God expect from men the life of angels. If any are dissatisfied with the account of things here given, I would beg leave to ask them whether unprofitable talk be not a sinful wasting of time? and whether that must not render a man in some degree criminal before God?” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For by thy words ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, by the evidence of thy words, as well as of thy tempers and works, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thou shall be justified, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Shalt be either acquitted or condemned; since by the tenor of these the disposition of thy heart is shown, and thy true character discovered. Therefore these shall be produced in evidence for or against thee at the great day, and by this evidence thou shalt then stand or fall.",
        "children": []
      },
